title: Ask HN: Any (ex) US Consulate officers on HN?
text:
I run a US non-immigrant community portal that has over 300K monthly visits. I sense there is a bigger opportunity to collaborate with the US consulate officer. I've tried LinkedIn, searching gov records, et al to contact ex-consulate officers. As a last attempt, want to give it a try here.

Any help with leads (forums/groups/websites) on where I can find them is really appreciated. If you (or your network) are an ex-US consulate officer, kindly drop an email to saradhi@extracttable.com. TIA.

title: Ask HN: What do you think would make Youtube better for you?
text:
Hey folks!

I am Amine, a web developer and I want to build a platform to make your Youtube experience much better by cutting the fluff out of your way and make your recommendations much worth it by giving you more control on what you want to watch and not be stuck in a content loop anymore.

So I would like to know: What do you don't like about the Youtube algorithm? What would make it better in your opinion?

Ask HN: Are those who live in UTC+7 to UTC+10 hard to get any remote works?
text:
Hi, I live in Indonesia (UTC+7), this is just something I am thinking (feeling) currently, is getting remote US works/contracts/jobs in these timezones hard (harder)? Especially when looking at some remote works, you either have to be in US, EU, or some non Asian countries. And if there are any, well, admittedly, the job may not fit with my rates.

What are some obstacles that prospect employers face when they can't hire someone from these timezones?

(I can be a bit subjective, please do correct me if you find this to be incorrect)

For a bit more context, I'm a Full stack Laravel developer.
